(68,1,"2019-04-18 06:33:05","2019-04-18 06:33:05","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Apollo Isha Vidhya Niketan was perplexed about how the young rural school pupils could jot down their first flight stories without having ever really traveled by air. Having known about the little daydreamers, Airytails gave a chance for the rural school pupils to participate in the contest – the rural school pupils could use their imagination to create their own first flight stories. And thus the rural school pupils began their first imaginary take off! Four of them flew to places like Tokyo, Kathmandu, Bengaluru. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:more -->\n<!--more-->\n<!-- /wp:more -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They soared in their own dreams and landed down with their own imaginary stories. The original make-believe stories of four pupils were submitted successfully on December 17, 2018.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":55} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/04-1024x747.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-55\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>#1 Excerpts from Jayani Sree’s first flight story:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I flew for the first time by Emirates plane to Tokyo. It was an exciting trip. When I entered the plane, the air-hostess greeted me with a beautiful smile. I got the window seat. After some time, the flight took off, it was a breathtaking moment! In no time, the flight was in the air and I was in cloud nine, I was really flying!”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Having snacks at home and in school has been quite common in my life, but having snacks in air, ah, that was lovely!”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I watched movies on the plane, I read books on the plane. I waited eagerly for the landing. The time came for me to see the landing. Ah, I reached Tokyo! My first flight experience was amazing!!”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->","Enabling Young Minds to Fly High – The Story of AIRYTAILS","","inherit","closed","closed","","54-revision-v1","","","2019-04-18 06:33:05","2019-04-18 06:33:05","",54,"http://blog.local/54-revision-v1/",0,"revision","",0),
(69,1,"2019-04-18 06:34:19","2019-04-18 06:34:19","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The moment of seeing the #Winner Alert! on WhatsApp is unforgettable to all of our four young writers. It was exhilarating to read the Airytails CEO and Founder, J S Ashwini ’s statement on Facebook: “We couldn’t stop ourselves from choosing these 4 kids from Isha Vidhya Chittor as winners for our #firstflight contest. I’m sure everyone would agree after reading their amazing imagination for how #firstflight would be?” The applause for our school pupils on Facebook is overwhelming, indeed. Airytails felt to give more to our humble young pupils.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Giving More</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the first time, Airytails collaborated with Sanahi Studio, Bengaluru and made an amazing painting. On February 05, 2019, Airytails visited Apollo Isha Vidhya Niketan – Aragonda to give away the painting and to congratulate the four winners of the #firstflight contest. The four pupils were ecstatic to receive the winner’s certificates from Airytails.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":52} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://blog.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/02.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-52\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Besides, they were pampered with a few sheets of paper planes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:more -->\n<!--more-->\n<!-- /wp:more -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before leaving our school, Airytails generously gave away the sheets of paper planes to the enthusiastic students and also helped the students make paper planes. Both the Airytails team and Apollo Isha Vidhya Niketan students enjoyed themselves in making the paper planes and flying them the farthest, of course!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->","AERO inspire at Isha Vidhya Inspiring Rural India","","inherit","closed","closed","","51-revision-v1","","","2019-04-18 06:34:19","2019-04-18 06:34:19","",51,"http://blog.local/51-revision-v1/",0,"revision","",0),
